# 6. 一緒にいられるのは

Saki: So you were out shopping, and got into a fight...
Female High Schooler A: Yes, we got completely fed up with each other and split up. Before I knew it, I was here.
Saki: That's terrible...
Saki: (They came here to have fun, but they're both all alone now after their argument. That's so sad...)
Shiho: Umm... We should probably apologize for asking you so many personal questions.
Female High Schooler A: No, I actually feel a lot better now after telling you two...!
Female High Schooler A: Also, thinking back on what happened, our argument really began over something tiny. We basically fought over nothing...
Saki: Nothing?
Female High Schooler A: So, when we met up earlier, she told me that she forgot to have breakfast.
Female High Schooler A: Then, I responded, “You stayed up all night again, didn't you? You gotta get plenty of sleep and eat right.” And then she got mad at me...
Shiho: I don't see anything wrong with what you said...
Female High Schooler A: But I do go a little too far sometimes.
Female High Schooler A: Yes, I am bothered by these sorts of little things, but she's also a bit of a mess, you know?
Female High Schooler A: I'll point that out, and we end up in an argument like we did earlier.
Shiho: I see... You have the exact opposite personalities.
Saki: Don't they remind you of us when we were kids?
Female High Schooler A: What?
Saki: You see, we're also childhood friends. And we argued all the time when we were little.
Shiho: Now that you mention it, we are pretty similar...
Female High Schooler A: Excuse me, but how did you two make up each time?
Saki: Hmm... How did we make up?
Shiho: Honami or Ichika usually stepped in to stop us every time we began arguing...
Saki: That's right! They did all sorts of stuff to help us make up!
Shiho: Yeah. They had us have snacks together, or play at the park...
Shiho: Neither of us would budge in the beginning, but we usually realized how silly we were being.
Saki: Hehe. Before we knew it, we'd completely forget about whatever argument we were having.
Shiho: Also... Whenever we'd fight, you'd suddenly apologize out of nowhere, Saki.
Saki: That's because it always hurt really bad when we were fighting. And not getting to play with you always made me so sad...
Female High Schooler A: We might not be any different.
Saki & Shiho: Huh?
Female High Schooler A: My friend is usually the one who takes the first step in patching things up...
Female High Schooler A: She'll share fun videos with me or invite me out somewhere. We'll talk and laugh, and go back to being friends like nothing had happened.
Shiho: I've never really thought about us like this before, but it really isn't common for people with completely different personalities to stay friends for years and years.
Female High Schooler A: That's a good point... A part of me just figured that we'd never be rid of each other.
Female High Schooler A: But maybe the real reason we've stuck together all this time is because she makes a real effort to stay with me...
Saki: (She makes a real effort...)
Saki: (We split apart for a time... But we were able to get our band back together and become friends again.)
Saki: (Those things alone made me unbelievably happy...)
Saki: (But we're able to stay together like this now because they're all doing their best to make sure we don't get scattered to the wind again.)
Saki: (In other words...)
Saki: It's hard to realize this kind of thing while just living day to day...
Saki: But it really makes you want to say, “Thank you!” to the people who try so hard to stay by your side, huh?
Shiho: Saki...
Female High Schooler A: I agree... It's pretty amazing, isn't it?
Female High Schooler A: I... I want to tell her.
Saki: Hehe. In that case, we recommend writing her a card!
Shiho: Yes, we can help you further if you like.
Female High Schooler A: Thank you very much! Then, if it's alright, I think I'd like to make my friend a message card.
Saki: Yes, of course!
Emu: Hehe☆ I'm so glad we managed to find the perfect puppet for you, MEIKO. It's so cute♪
MEIKO: <Hehe. I'm looking forward to giving it a voice!>
MEIKO: <So, Emu! Let's get this show on the road.>
Emu: Yeah!
Emu: “White Day is just around the corner! I really wanna tell my friend just how much I appreciate them!”
Puppet: <I have just the thing for you, Emu! Here, take this♪>
Emu: “Wow, this card's so beautiful!”
Puppet: <Why don't you take this card, decorate it and write a nice message for your friend?>
Puppet: <It'll be a true one-of-a-kind!>
Emu: “I wanna try doing that! Can you show me how to decorate it, Ms. Puppet?”
Puppet: <Of course! Let's work on it together!>
Shopper: What's going on over there? A puppet show?
Shopper: Hey, what's she making?
Emu: “I just gotta put these stickers on, and... It's finished☆”
Puppet: <Nice work, Emu! What a lovely card!>
Emu: “Thanks! So, Ms. Puppet, this is for you!”
Emu: “Thank you for always playing with me!”
Puppet: <Oh...! Hehe. Thank you as well!>
Emu: “Hehe♪ I hope we keep being friends forever and ever!”
Shopper: Writing message cards sounds fun. Wanna go take a look?
Shopper: Yeah. Let's go check out the event area in the courtyard.
Emu: Oh, MEIKO, our plan's working!
MEIKO: <We did it, Emu!>
???: ...
Emu: (Huh...? That girl just keeps staring at the sign for the event...)
Emu: (Does this mean she wants to make a message card for someone?)
Emu: Hello! Are you interested in writing some message cards?
Female High Schooler B: Oh, no. I'm okay. I was just thinking that my friend would really enjoy this event.
Emu: I see! You came here with your friend today?
Female High Schooler B: Yeah. We came to grab some donuts here, since we heard that they're pretty good.
Emu: Oh, they smell really yummy!
Emu: Wait... Where is your friend?
Female High Schooler B: Oh... We actually got into an argument a bit ago.
Emu: What?! You got into an argument...?
Female High Schooler B: At this point, it's sort of a regular occurrence.
Female High Schooler B: I mean, she's just so nit-picky. “You need to eat a proper breakfast”, or “your skirt's too short, fix it”, that kind of thing...
Female High Schooler B: So I said, “What are you, my mom?” After that, things got really out of hand.
Female High Schooler B: And we both ended up storming off.
Emu: I see...
Emu: It sounds like she cares about you a lot!
Female High Schooler B: Huh?
Emu: So, I also have a friend in class who's always telling me not to run in the corridor because it's dangerous, and how I'm going to catch a cold if I don't dress warmer...
Emu: I feel bad and apologize every time, but I also feel a little happy.
Female High Schooler B: Happy?
Emu: Hehe. Because her saying that means she doesn't want me to trip and get hurt, or feel gross after picking up a nasty cold.
Emu: Which is why my heart feels really warm every time!
Female High Schooler B: ... I see. You're such a nice person.
Emu: Huh?
Female High Schooler B: And you're right. When she said what she did, I got really irritated...
Female High Schooler B: But she wouldn't scold me like that if she didn't care about me.
Female High Schooler B: In hindsight... I feel like I should show her at least some appreciation.
Emu: Then, what if you did that now? By writing her a message card!
Female High Schooler B: Huh...?
Emu: You could give it to her with the donuts... I bet you two will be smiling like peas in a pod afterwards!
Female High Schooler B: I'm not sure I can make her a good card... Could you help me with that?
Emu: Yes! I'll give you all the help you need!
Female High Schooler B: Haha. Okay. Then, I'll give it a try.
Female High Schooler B: Oh, I should see if she'll agree to meet up again later. Let's see... <Can we talk again today one more time?>
Female High Schooler B: Oh, she replied... Wait, what?!
Emu: Huh...?
